`вҳ… Insight в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ`
**Why `|| 0` in `snapToGrid`?** `Math.round(-0 / 0.5)` can produce `-0` in JavaScript. The `|| 0` coerces `-0` to `0`, ensuring consistent grid keys (no `"-0,0,0"` vs `"0,0,0"` mismatch). A subtle but important detail for `Set`-based occupancy lookups.

**Bonus utility: `gridKey`** вҖ” The PRD didn't specify it, but the implementation added a `gridKey(coord): string` helper that converts `{x,y,z}` to `"x,y,z"` strings for O(1) `Set`/`Map` lookups. This is used by `isSlotOccupied` and will be essential for US-012 (structural integrity BFS) and US-018 (pattern matching).
